question: Ellen has 3 jars of frosting in her cupboard. Each jar of frosting can decorate 11 muffins. Ellen wants to bake enough muffins to use up all of her frosting. If each rack holds 11 muffins, how many racks worth of muffins should she bake?
answer:
She has enough frosting for 3 * 11 = <<3*11=33>>33 muffins.
She needs 33 / 11 = <<33/11=3>>3 racks to bake all of the muffins.
#### 3
